text: Gum 15 is a nebula from the Gum catalog, located in the constellation of Vela, about 3,000 light-years from Earth.http://www.sci-news.com/astronomy/science- star-forming-region-gum15-02037.html It is shaped by aggressive winds flowing from the stars within and around it. The bright star in the center of the nebula is HD 74804, a double star.http://simbad.u-strasbg.fr/simbad/sim- id?Ident=HD++74804 ==References== Category:H II regions Category:Vela (constellation)
title: Gum 15
